<div class="bz_comment_text">Attempting to call a function with more than 65536 arguments results in a RangeError being thrown.

How to reproduce:

var i, l, a, s;
for (i = 0, l = 65537, a = []; i &lt; l; i++) a.push(60);
s = String.fromCharCode.apply(String, a);

Expected result:

The arguments are applied to the method.

Actual result:

The following error is thrown: &quot;RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded.&quot;</div>
    </div>
    
    

        
        
